The Lagos State Government on Saturday, discharged 40 COVID-19 patients. This was disclosed in a statement on the state ministry of health official Twitter page. The discharged patients consists of 22 females and 23 males. The tweet read: “#COVID19Lagos Update, 45 COVID19 Lagos patients; 22 females & 23 males, all Nigerians have been discharged from our Isolation facilities to reunite with the society.” Meanwhile, as of Saturday morning , Nigeria has recorded 245 new confirmed cases of coronavirus. This brings the total of cases in the country to 7,267. COVID-19: Lagos Govt confirms 176 new cases as toll hits 1683 Lagos discharges four COVID-19 patients Coronavirus: Mother, baby among recovered patients of COVID-19 in Lagos